# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:7
translate german counselorconversation5_0c2aa4f4:

    # pc "I kind of miss Brazil."
    pc "Ich vermisse Brasilien irgendwie."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:8
translate german counselorconversation5_2ec566c7:

    # sc "I bet. Was it nice there?"
    sc "Das glaube ich dir. War es schön dort?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:9
translate german counselorconversation5_ef088408:

    # pc "It was, most of the time."
    pc "Ja, meistens."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:10
translate german counselorconversation5_ffefa487:

    # sc "Most of the time?"
    sc "Meistens?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:11
translate german counselorconversation5_f6155a33:

    # pc "Well the places that I stayed at were very nice."
    pc "Nun, die Orte, an denen ich gewohnt habe, waren sehr schön."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:12
translate german counselorconversation5_444ece6f:

    # pc "But Brazil has a sort of split-personality."
    pc "Aber Brasilien hat so eine Art gespaltene Persönlichkeit."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:13
translate german counselorconversation5_9247b82f:

    # pc "It's absolutely beautiful in most of the places that I stayed."
    pc "An den meisten Orten, an denen ich gewohnt habe, ist es absolut wunderschön."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:14
translate german counselorconversation5_6ce76dfd:

    # pc "But occasionally, I saw the other side, where people were so poor and hungry and had no way to better themselves."
    pc "Aber gelegentlich habe ich die andere Seite gesehen, wo die Menschen so arm und hungrig waren und keine Möglichkeit hatten, ihr Leben zu verbessern."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:15
translate german counselorconversation5_64352ea1:

    # sc "That must have been eye-opening."
    sc "Das muss dir die Augen geöffnet haben."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:16
translate german counselorconversation5_ad0a9fab:

    # pc "It was. I know that people are like that in places,"
    pc "Das hat es. Ich weiß, dass es an manchen Orten Menschen so geht,"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:17
translate german counselorconversation5_b47c5612:

    # pc "But it was so strange to see all of that, then go back to the dorm where I was living and nobody seemed to care."
    pc "aber es war so seltsam, all das zu sehen und dann zurück in das Wohnheim zu gehen, in dem ich wohnte, und niemand schien sich darum zu kümmern."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:18
translate german counselorconversation5_ba9df9c6:

    # sc "We tend to ignore the nasty things in life that don't affect us personally."
    sc "Wir neigen dazu, die schlimmen Dinge im Leben zu ignorieren, die uns nicht persönlich betreffen."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:19
translate german counselorconversation5_34e34dc1:

    # sc "It's a sort of coping mechanism. If we were constantly worried about every bad thing happening, we'd probably have a stroke."
    sc "Das ist eine Art Bewältigungsstrategie. Wenn wir uns ständig Sorgen um alles machen würden, was Schlimmes passiert, bekämen wir wahrscheinlich einen Herzinfarkt."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:20
translate german counselorconversation5_e46768d7:

    # pc "I guess so, it's just hard to put some of that stuff out of my mind."
    pc "Das mag sein, aber es fällt mir einfach schwer, manche dieser Dinge aus meinem Kopf zu verbannen."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:21
translate german counselorconversation5_2426cfe6:

    # sc "You shouldn't. You should keep it there. It will make you a better person."
    sc "Das solltest du auch nicht. Du solltest sie im Kopf behalten. Das macht dich zu einem besseren Menschen."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:22
translate german counselorconversation5_4a449be8:

    # sc "Know that these things are happening, and know that you are privileged to have the life that you have."
    sc "Sei dir bewusst, dass diese Dinge geschehen, und sei dir bewusst, dass du das Privileg hast, das Leben zu führen, das du führst."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:23
translate german counselorconversation5_e88d7ffc:

    # pc "You're right."
    pc "Du hast recht."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:25
translate german counselorconversation5_067380d2:

    # sc "You have a good heart. Have you seen The Breakfast Club?"
    sc "Du hast ein gutes Herz. Hast du „The Breakfast Club“ gesehen?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:28
translate german counselorconversation5_a6773fcb:

    # pc "Sure. Everybody has seen that, right?"
    pc "Klar. Den hat doch jeder gesehen, oder?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:30
translate german counselorconversation5_8c93b784:

    # pc "I haven't seen it."
    pc "Ich habe ihn nicht gesehen."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:31
translate german counselorconversation5_14e2d7b8:

    # sc "Well there's a line in it that Ally Sheedy says."
    sc "Nun, da gibt es eine Zeile, die Ally Sheedy sagt."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:32
translate german counselorconversation5_314554fe:

    # sc "She says, \"When you grow up, your heart dies.\""
    sc "Sie sagt: „Wenn man erwachsen wird, stirbt das Herz.“"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:33
translate german counselorconversation5_67060d07:

    # sc "And it's true for a lot of people. As they grow up, they become jaded and cynical and stop caring about things."
    sc "Und für viele Menschen trifft das zu. Wenn sie erwachsen werden, werden sie abgestumpft und zynisch und hören auf, sich um Dinge zu kümmern."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:34
translate german counselorconversation5_9123a037:

    # sc "But you're still young. You have a good heart. Don't let it die, okay?"
    sc "Aber du bist noch jung. Du hast ein gutes Herz. Lass es nicht sterben, okay?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:35
translate german counselorconversation5_dd9a629d:

    # pc "I won't."
    pc "Das werde ich nicht."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:37
translate german counselorconversation5_37653c95:

    # sc "Okay, well you better get to class."
    sc "Okay, dann geh lieber zum Unterricht."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:38
translate german counselorconversation5_a8c43555:

    # pc "Okay, I'll see you next time Gertrude."
    pc "Okay, bis zum nächsten Mal, Gertrude."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:39
translate german counselorconversation5_1b784c07:

    # sc "Bye, [pcname]."
    sc "Tschüss, [pcname]."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:40
translate german counselorconversation5_e4b88e88:

    # "With that, I stand up and head to class."
    "Damit stehe ich auf und gehe zum Unterricht."

